site/index.html:422:                    <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Claude session keys, ChatGPT session cookies, and Gemini API keys are stored through macOS Keychain-backed boundaries. Diagnostics are sanitized and credentials never leave your machine.</p>
site/index.html:443:                    <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Optional quota visibility uses a local browser session when configured. If ChatGPT is unavailable or rejected, Claude monitoring continues.</p>
site/index.html:447:                    <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Optional Gemini status visibility uses an API key entered in Settings and stored in Keychain, with sanitized status diagnostics.</p>
site/index.html:462:                            <li>Claude session keys, ChatGPT session cookies, and Gemini API keys are stored locally through Keychain boundaries.</li>
site/index.html:464:                            <li>Usage exports are local JSON files under <code>~/.pinemeter/usage.json</code>, with legacy <code>~/.claudemeter/usage.json</code> compatibility for older scripts.</li>
site/index.html:472:                            <li>Unavailable, rejected, and rate-limited provider states show sanitized copyable errors without raw credentials.</li>
