CHANGELOG.md:147:- Initial ClaudeMeter macOS menu bar app
README.md:88:Pinemeter can import your existing Claude session from local browser cookies. Sign in to [claude.ai](https://claude.ai) in a supported browser, then choose **Import from Browser** in the setup wizard or Settings.
README.md:143:- **Provider unavailable, rejected, or rate limited:** Open Settings and use the provider-specific repair, reconnect, or clear actions. The UI shows sanitized status and copyable error text without raw credentials.
README.md:144:- **Reset local state:** Clear the affected provider in Settings, sign in again in your browser if needed, then import or paste the credential again.
README.md:149:Pinemeter exports Claude usage data to `~/.pinemeter/usage.json` for use with external tools like Claude Code statusline scripts, shell prompts, or custom dashboards. For compatibility with earlier ClaudeMeter-era scripts, Pinemeter may also write a legacy `~/.claudemeter/usage.json` copy.
README.md:222:xcodebuild clean build -project Pinemeter.xcodeproj -scheme Pinemeter -configuration Debug
README.md:225:xcodebuild test \
README.md:248:- Claude session keys are stored securely in macOS Keychain (encrypted, device-local only)
README.md:251:- Browser import reads local browser cookies only to extract the selected provider credential/session material
README.md:252:- Diagnostic and acquisition state is sanitized; raw cookies, tokens, headers, and API keys are not written to diagnostics
README.md:253:- Usage data is cached locally (unencrypted, contains usage percentages/status only)
